@using Postal
@model Inview.Epi.EpiFund.Web.Models.Emails.ConfirmationCRNoteSellerFormSubmittalEmail

To: @Model.Email
From: USCREonline <info@uscreonline.com>
Subject: CRE Note Liquidation Profile Upload Received
Content-type: text/html;charset=utf-8
<html>
<body>
    <p><img src="http://uscreonline.com/content/images/uscrelogowithbg.png" /></p>

<p>Dear @Model.Name,</p>

<p>Welcome!  Thank you for commencing your US CRE Online Commercial Investment Real Estate Data Portal relationship online with USC.  Your registration and Commercial Note asset data upload commencement included your acceptance and acknowledgement of the (1) USC Confidentiality and Non-Disclosure Non-Compete Agreement, and execution of the (2) USC &#91;Data Storage & Internet Portal Agreement&#93; specific to the subject CRE Asset captioned herein.  Please verify that the following summary data on your newly created CRE Asset Data at your USC data file is accurate:</p>

    <table class="table">
        <tr>
            <td>Asset ID#:</td>
            <td>@Html.DisplayFor(s => s.AssetDescription.AssetNumber)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Asset Type:</td>
            <td>Private Mortgage Note Secured by CRE</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Property address:</td>
            <td>@Html.DisplayFor(s => s.AssetDescription.AssetAddressOneLineFormattedString)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Property Type:</td>
            <td>@Html.DisplayFor(s => s.AssetDescription.Description)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>APN:</td>
            <td>@Html.DisplayFor(s => s.APN)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Vesting Entity:</td>
            <td>@Html.DisplayFor(s => s.VestingEntity)</td>
        </tr>
     <tr>
            <td>Corp Officer:</td>
            <td>@Html.DisplayFor(s => s.CorpOfficer)</td>
        </tr>
    </table>


<p>You are in complete &#91;user&#93; control of the Data File for the above captioned Asset ID #.  All Data Files are fully encrypted with USC operating within multiple layers of firewalls making it virtually impossible for any unauthorized party to have access to your data file and uploaded documentation.  You will be able to Publish and Un-Publish your Asset and or selected Portfolio of Assets to the US CRE Online Community of NAR, MBA and Private Investor db Members at any time.  Communications between you and all respondents to your &#91;Asset Memorandum Publications&#93; is always initiated through fully secured and private intra-site e mails through your respective &#91;&#34;My USC Page&#34;&#93;: thus you will not be sharing any of your contact data with respondents until you initiate the invitation.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 20px;"><span style="color: red;">Note:</span>  all communications from &#91;Asset Memorandum Publication&#93; respondents are required to come from qualified principal investors registered at and with US CRE Online.com.  Verifiable Proof of Funds and Corporate Resumes are standard, requisite attachments to all LOI submittals to USC Asset Holders with published Assets.  Automated &#34;Letters of Intent to Acquire Assets&#34; are available for all USC Registrants at any CRE Asset View page.  We encourage you to review the template to become familiar with it should you elect to utilize the LOI in the future.  </p>

<p>Should any of our registered principals submit a CRE Search Criteria request form through US CRE Online that qualifies your property, you will receive an automated notification of said Registrant&#39;s interest.  You will be able to further communications with each such USC Registrant through USC&#39;s fully secured and private intra-site e mails at your respective &#91;&#34;My USC Page&#34;&#93;.</p>

<p style="margin-left: 20px;"><span style="color: red;">Courtesy request:</span>  please do not hesitate to communicate any thoughts you may have for site, data presentation, and or automated communications upgrades to USC through our &#91;Contact Us&#93; site page.  US CRE Online is here to fully serve the US CRE Investment Community.  Thank you.</p>

    <p>Thank you for being a valued Principal Investor Registrant of United States Commercial Real Estate Online, LLC.  It is our honor and privilege to provide the defined CRE data services to the investment community.</p>

<p>The Professional Staff</p>
<p>US CRE Online, LLC</p>
</body>
</html>
